        "message": "fix release.yml: continue-on-error Package + upload-artifact + always push binary\n\nThe Windows Package step keeps tripping on PowerShell quoting / Compress-Archive\nedge cases. Three safety nets:\n\n  1. continue-on-error: true on Package — even if archive fails, the binary\n     was built successfully and we can still publish the .exe raw\n  2. actions/upload-artifact@v4 — explicit artifact upload as a back-channel\n     (so users can always pull the .exe from the workflow run even if the\n     GitHub Release step itself fails)\n  3. files: list the .exe directly under dist/, alongside the .tar.gz/.zip\n\nThis means: in the worst case users still get a working binary, and in the\ncommon case they get binary + tarball + zip.",
